Package org.forgerock.openam.entitlement.rest.query

Class QueryFilterVisitorAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openam.entitlement.rest.query.QueryFilterVisitorAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.forgerock.util.query.QueryFilterVisitor<Set<SearchFilter>,​Set<SearchFilter>,​org.forgerock.json.JsonPointer>
    public abstract class QueryFilterVisitorAdapter
extends Object
implements org.forgerock.util.query.QueryFilterVisitor<Set<SearchFilter>,​Set<SearchFilter>,​org.forgerock.json.JsonPointer>
    Abstract base class for building converters that map CREST query filters to a set of entitlement search filters. All QueryFilterVisitor methods are implemented to throw UnsupportedOperationException. If a particular query filter type is to be supported, the relevant method should be overridden to implement the required mapping.
    Since:
    12.0.0

      • comparison

        protected SearchFilter comparison​(String field,
                                  SearchFilter.Operator operator,
                                  Object valueAssertion)
        Attempts to convert the given field name, operator and value into an appropriate SearchFilter instance. The conversion used depends on the QueryAttribute configured for this field in the queryAttributes map.
        Parameters:
        field - Non null, The name of a queryable Application attribute.
        operator - Non null, The query operator to use when comparing the field value to the valueAssertion.
        valueAssertion - Non null, The value with which the Application field's value should be compared.

      • unsupportedFilterOperation

        protected UnsupportedOperationException unsupportedFilterOperation​(String filterType)
        Factory method for UnsupportedOperationException to indicate no support for a CREST filter type.
        Parameters:
        filterType - The type of filter that is not supported
        Returns:
        UnsupportedOperationException
